== References == {{Reflist|30em}}
{{authority control}}

'''Ismail Jumaih''' is a Maldivian actor.
==Career== In 2016, Jumaih made his film debut in Hussain Munawwar's ''[[Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee]]'' alongside [[Aminath Rishfa]] and [[Ahmed Azmeel]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sun.mv/70075 |title=Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee's First show full, Tickets available at four spots |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Sun'' |date=26 February 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606110604/https://sun.mv/70075 |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> Critics panned the film and considered his performance as Sham, to be "boring" while criticising the character development.<ref name=NeyngiYaaruVakivee>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/14598 |title=The actual reason of "Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee" |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Avas'' |author=Nadheem, Ahmed |date=6 April 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606101756/https://avas.mv/14598 |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> However, Ahmed Jaishan of ''Vaguthu'', found Jumaih's acting to be "natural and impressive" considering his debut role and picked him as the "biggest highlight" from the "disappointing" film.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vaguthu.mv/reports/391659/ |title=Neyngi Yaaru vakivee: Movie Review |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Vaguthu'' |author=Jaishan, Ahmed |date=5 March 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603181732/http://www.vaguthu.mv/reports/391659/ |archivedate=3 June 2016 |accessdate=3 June 2016}}</ref> Despite the negative reviews, the film did an average business at the end of its run.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/entertainment/391632/ |title=Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee premiered to a positive response |language=Dhivehi |publisher=''Vaguthu'' |author=Jaishan, Ahmed |date=5 March 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606110957/http://www.vaguthu.mv/evaguthu/entertainment/391632/ |archivedate=6 June 2016 |accessdate=6 June 2016}}</ref> Jumaih's another release of the year came with Fathimath Nahula's horror film ''[[4426]]'', where he portrayed the role of Hanim, an aggressive member of the friends who gets trapped in a haunted house.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/13832 |title=This time its not a "Nahu-styled" film, A revelation |language=Dhivehi |work=Avas |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=26 February 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330052428/https://avas.mv/13832 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> Upon release, the film received mostly positive reviews from critics. Ahmed Nadheem of ''Avas'' labelled the film as a "masterpiece" and mentioned Jumaih to be the "surprising element" of the film.<ref name=4426review/> Complimenting the improvements he showed from ''Neyngi Yaaru Vakivee'', Nadheem picked his role as the second best performance of the film; "With compliments to Nahula for her character buliding, Jumaih was deep in the character of Hanim, portraying the role to its fullest".<ref name=4426review>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/24396 |title=4426 is Nahula's mastepiece |language=Dhivehi |work=Avas |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=21 October 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330060956/https://avas.mv/24396 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref> With twenty-five back-to-back housefull being screened, ''4426'' was declared as the highest grossing film of the year.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avas.mv/25919 |title=25 Housefull shows of 4426 screened! Now screening the last few shows |language=Dhivehi |work=Avas |date=20 November 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180330061815/https://avas.mv/25919 |deadurl=no |archivedate=30 March 2018 |accessdate=30 March 2018 |df=dmy-all}}</ref>
